The article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring October 2014 as National Cybersecurity Awareness Month. The proclamation highlights the importance of cybersecurity and the threats posed by cyber threats to the country's critical infrastructure, individual liberties, and the way of life of every American. It emphasizes the need to make cyberspace more secure and raise awareness about the role individuals can play in ensuring cybersecurity. The Department of Homeland Security's "Stop.Think.Connect." campaign is mentioned as a resource to empower individuals to take action and protect their private accounts and information. The proclamation also mentions the Cybersecurity Framework released by the administration and the investments being made to keep up with rapidly changing technology. The proclamation concludes by calling upon the people of the United States to observe National Cybersecurity Awareness Month with activities, events, and training that will enhance national security and resilience.